TITLE:: PanolaRational
summary:: an exact rational number used by Panola's duration spelling
categories:: Utils
related:: Classes/PanolaDurationSpeller

DESCRIPTION::
PanolaRational is a minimal exact rational (teletype::num/den::, always reduced, sign in the numerator,
denominator positive). It exists because SuperCollider has no rational type and because notation must not
be treated as floating point. Numerator and denominator are stored as Float-valued integers so the
arithmetic stays exact without overflowing SuperCollider's 32-bit Integer. It supports the strong::+ - * /::
operators and the comparison operators, plus construction from an Integer, a decimal String
(teletype::*fromDecimalString::), or a Float via a limit-denominator continued fraction
(teletype::*fromFloat::), e.g. teletype::0.3333333:: becomes teletype::1/3::.



CLASSMETHODS::

METHOD:: new
create a reduced rational num/den

ARGUMENT:: num
the numerator

ARGUMENT:: den
the denominator (default 1)

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: fromInteger
an Integer as n/1

ARGUMENT:: n
an Integer

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: pr_gcd
the greatest common divisor of two Float-valued integers (Euclid's algorithm), used to reduce fractions

ARGUMENT:: a
a Float-valued integer

ARGUMENT:: b
a Float-valued integer

returns:: a Float (the gcd)
METHOD:: pr_coerce
coerce a value to a PanolaRational: pass a PanolaRational through, wrap an Integer as n/1, or convert a Float via fromFloat (used by the arithmetic and comparison operators)

ARGUMENT:: x
a PanolaRational, Integer, or Float

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: fromFloat
the exact rational of a finite Float, with the denominator limited so common values snap to their intended fraction (e.g. 0.3333333 -> 1/3, 0.4 -> 2/5)

ARGUMENT:: x
a finite Float

ARGUMENT:: maxDenom
the largest allowed denominator (default 65536)

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: fromDecimalString
parse a decimal String such as "0.625" as an exact rational (5/8)

ARGUMENT:: s
a decimal String

returns:: a PanolaRational

INSTANCEMETHODS::

METHOD:: num
the numerator (a Float holding an exact integer)

returns:: a Float
METHOD:: den
the denominator (a Float holding an exact positive integer)

returns:: a Float
METHOD:: pr_init
initialize this rational from a raw numerator and denominator: force the sign into the numerator (denominator positive) and reduce by the gcd

ARGUMENT:: n
the raw numerator (a Float)

ARGUMENT:: d
the raw denominator (a Float)

returns:: this PanolaRational
METHOD:: limitDenominator
the closest rational to this value whose denominator is at most maxDenom (CPython Fraction.limit_denominator)

ARGUMENT:: maxDenom
the largest allowed denominator (default 65536)

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: negate
the negation of this value

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: neg
the negation of this value (alias of negate)

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: reciprocal
den/num as a PanolaRational

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: abs
the absolute value

returns:: a PanolaRational
METHOD:: isNegative
whether the value is negative

returns:: true if the value is < 0
METHOD:: isZero
whether the value is zero

returns:: true if the value is 0
METHOD:: numerator
the numerator as an Integer

returns:: the numerator as an Integer
METHOD:: denominator
the denominator as an Integer

returns:: the denominator as an Integer
METHOD:: asFloat
the value as a Float

returns:: the value as a Float
METHOD:: asInteger
the value truncated toward zero as an Integer

returns:: the value truncated toward zero as an Integer
METHOD:: asString
the value as "num/den"

returns:: the value as "num/den"

